#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.109:0.2"
msgid "11. Antavagga "
msgstr "11. Sides "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn22.109:0.3"
msgid "109. Sotāpannasutta "
msgstr "109. A Stream-Enterer "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli3.161, sc1
msgctxt "sn22.109:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ. "
msgstr "At Sāvatthī. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn22.109:1.2"
msgid "“Pañcime, bhikkhave, upādānakkhandhā. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, there are these five grasping aggregates. "

msgctxt "sn22.109:1.3"
msgid "Katame pañca? "
msgstr "What five? "

msgctxt "sn22.109:1.4"
msgid "Seyyathidaṃ—rūpupādānakkhandho … pe … viññāṇupādānakkhandho. "
msgstr "That is, the grasping aggregates of form, feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness. "

msgctxt "sn22.109:1.5"
msgid "Yato kho, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako imesaṃ pañcannaṃ upādānakkhandhānaṃ samudayañca atthaṅgamañca assādañca ādīnavañca nissaraṇañca yathābhūtaṃ pajānāti. "
msgstr "A noble disciple comes to truly understand these five grasping aggregates’ origin, ending, gratification, drawback, and escape. "

msgctxt "sn22.109:1.6"
msgid "Ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, ariyasāvako sotāpanno avinipātadhammo niyato sambodhiparāyano”ti. "
msgstr "Such a noble disciple is called a stream-enterer, not liable to be reborn in the underworld, bound for awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn22.109:1.7"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

